         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">[Society for the Ad]vancement of Science. ¶ […] melbourne ¶ . ¶ January] ¶  13th  ¶ 18 ¶ 90 ¶ Sir James Hector K.C.M.G., M.D. ¶ Dear Sir...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">M90.01.13</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">Edward Odlum to James Hector</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">MU 147, box 7 (13 January 1890), Museum of New Zealand Te Papa Tongarewa Archives, Wellington.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>[Society for the Ad]vancement of Science.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="font-variant: small-caps; ">[…] melbourne</seg>
               <seg>.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">January]<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">editorial addition</seg> — the letterhead and part of the date is obscured by one of M's calling cards which is pinned to the letter.</p>
               </note> 13th <seg>18</seg>90</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir James Hector K.C.M.G., M.D.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Sir</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Sir<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">sic.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I fully expected to meet you at the Science Association but on inquiry learn you have not been able to attend.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As I have a letter of introduction to you you from a mutual friend Mr Hammersley<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Hammersley makes no reference to M. </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="color: #0919ff; font-weight: bold; ">I would not expect it to do so. It was Hamersley who was friend of Hector and of Odlum</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> of Vancouver B. C. Canada I desire to call upon you on my arrival in New Zealand.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I shall leave Melbourne for Auckland the first steamer after Feby. 5th if possible.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Perhaps You would be able to secure for me a scientist's pass over the New Zealand Railways.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As I am travelling in scientific pursuits (Anthropology and Geology) the Victorian Government granted me a pass over various lines. By this means I am able to make more complete examinations of important districts than could otherwise be done.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I take the liberty of sending a card of introduction from Baron Von Mueller K.C.MG. &amp;c as well as the letter referred to above.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[…]<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The letter continues in this vein but makes no further mention of M.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">E. Odlum</p>
         </div>
